# linker-sim (Linkerbot) — CODEOWNERS
#
# GitHub uses this file to suggest reviewers for pull requests. Lines starting
# with # are comments. Each rule is: <path-pattern> <space-separated @owners>
#
# How to customize:
# - Replace @linkerbot with real GitHub usernames or @org/team-slug when known.
# - Add more specific paths above broader ones; when multiple patterns match a
#   file, the last matching line wins.
# - See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Default (everything) ---
* @linkerbot

# --- Asset layer (components, workstations, generated artifacts) ---
/assets/ @linkerbot

# --- Sim runtime (backends, controllers, tasks, envs, registry) ---
/sim/ @linkerbot

# --- Composer + validators + CI drift gate ---
/tools/ @linkerbot

# --- Hydra entrypoints + replay scripts ---
/scripts/ @linkerbot

# --- Tests ---
/tests/ @linkerbot

# --- CI / Community ---
/.github/ @linkerbot

# --- Documentation ---
*.md @linkerbot
